article.description: Samir Stewart had 13 points as Manhattan edged past Canisius 70-65 on Sunday.
article.headline: Stewart scores 13 to lift Manhattan over Canisius 70-65
article.linkText: Stewart scores 13 to lift Manhattan over Canisius 70-65
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Samir Stewart had 13 points as Manhattan edged past Canisius 70-65 on Sunday. Warren Williams had 12 points for Manhattan (9-17, 7-7 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Tykei Greene added 11 points. Tyler Reynolds had 10 points for the visiting team. Jibreel Faulkner scored a career-high 20 points and had seven rebounds for the Golden Griffins (12-14, 9-5). Takal Molson added 15 points. Jonathan Sanks had 10 points. Manhattan matches up against Iona at home on Friday. Canisius faces Monmouth on the road on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
